quran[16]{c,v,t}:
  36,55,"Indeed, on that Day the people of Paradise will be busy enjoying themselves,"
  36,56,"they and their spouses will be reclining on couches in the shade."
  36,57,"They will have therein fruits and all what they ask for."
  36,58,"“Peace”: a word from a Most Merciful Lord."
  36,59,"“Stand apart [from the believers] this Day, O wicked ones!"
  36,60,"Did I not command you, O children of Adam, not to worship Satan, for he is your sworn enemy,"
  36,61,"but to worship Me? This is a straight path."
  36,62,"He had already misled great multitudes of you. Did you not then have sense?"
  36,63,"This is the Hell that you were promised."
  36,64,"Burn in it Today for your disbelief.”"
  36,65,"Today We will seal up their mouths, and their hands will speak to Us, and their feet will testify to all what they used to do."
  36,66,"If We willed, We could have taken away their sight, so they would rush to find their way, but then how could they see?"
  36,67,"And if We willed, We could have paralyzed them in their places, so they could neither move forward nor backward."
  36,68,"Whomsoever We give a long life, We cause his strength to decline. Do they not then understand?"
  36,69,"We have not taught him poetry, nor is it fitting for him. This is only a Reminder and a clear Qur’an"
  36,70,"so that he may warn those who are truly alive and establish the argument against the disbelievers."